**Note:**  
Given the limited customization options for mainstream movie streaming and rating apps, the top two provide notable customization in watchlists and interface themes, while many of the others offer standard user experience with less customization. IMDb and Letterboxd are widely recognized for robust user-defined watchlists and sharing features[2][3][4]. The remaining apps are included as leading content platforms, but their customization capabilities are typically more limited, focusing mainly on streaming or basic watchlists. For full transparency, this ranking is ordered with the strongest customization features first, as your ranking criteria specify. However, only a subset of these apps (IMDb, Letterboxd, and a few others) offer significant interface, theme, or functionality customization.